Solution:
Let each person be a point in the plane.  Draw a line segment connecting two points if and only if the corresponding people shake hands.  We want to count the number of line segments.

Each point can be connected to at most 22 other points.  Thus, the total number of line segments is at most $23 \cdot 22/2 = 253.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.5 cm);

int i, j;

for (i = 0; i <= 22; ++i) {
for (j = i + 1; j <= 22; ++j) {
draw((i,j)--(i + 1,j - 1));
}}

for (i = 0; i <= 22; ++i) {
draw((i,0)--(i,23));
draw((0,i)--(23,i));
}

label("$\vdots$", (-0.5,11.5));
label("$\cdots$", (11.5,23.5));
[/asy]

This maximum is achieved when we draw the above diagram, so the maximum number of handshakes is $\boxed{253}.$

Solution:
Recall that $n!$ is defined as $n\cdot(n-1)\cdot(n-2)\cdots 3\cdot 2\cdot 1$. Thus, we have: \begin{align*}
5\cdot5! + 4\cdot4!+4! &= 5\cdot(5\cdot4\cdot3\cdot2\cdot1) + 4\cdot(4\cdot3\cdot2\cdot1) + 4\cdot3\cdot2\cdot1 \\
&= 600 + 96 + 24 \\
&= \boxed{720}.
\end{align*}

